summary:
The Security Council:

Reaffirms previous resolutions and statements on Somalia, particularly the arms embargo established by resolution 733 (1992);

Recalls exemptions to the arms embargo for the African Union Mission in Somalia (AMISOM) and for States providing security sector assistance;

Reaffirms Somalia's sovereignty, territorial integrity, and unity;

Supports the Djibouti Peace Agreement and Transitional Federal Charter (TFC) as the basis for a lasting settlement;

Urges Somali leaders to continue political dialogue;

Commends the Special Representative of the Secretary-General, Mr. Ahmedou Ould-Abdallah;

Takes note of the Monitoring Group's report and condemns arms flows to Somalia;

Insists on strict enforcement of the arms embargo;

Determines the situation in Somalia remains a threat to international peace and security;

Acting under Chapter VII:

1. Stresses States' obligation to comply with the arms embargo and resolution 1844 (2008);
2. Intends to consider action to improve implementation of these measures;
3. Decides to extend the Monitoring Group's mandate for 12 months, with an expanded mandate to:
	* Continue tasks outlined in resolutions 1587 (2005) and 1844 (2008);
	* Investigate revenue sources used for arms embargo violations;
	* Investigate transport routes and facilities used for arms embargo violations;
	* Refine and update information on individuals and entities violating the embargo.
The Security Council:

1. Decides to establish a Monitoring Group to:

(a) assist the Committee in carrying out its mandate;

(b) monitor and enforce the arms embargo;

(c) gather information on violations of the arms embargo;

(d) make recommendations on strengthening the arms embargo;

(e) present information to the Committee as needed;

(f) continue making recommendations based on previous reports of the Panel of Experts and Monitoring Group;

(g) work closely with the Committee on specific recommendations;

(h) identify areas to strengthen States' capacities in the region;

(i) provide a midterm briefing and monthly progress reports;

(j) submit a final report covering all tasks;

2. Requests the Secretary-General to make necessary financial arrangements;

3. Reaffirms paragraphs 4, 5, 7, 8, and 10 of resolution 1519 (2003);

4. Requests the Committee to consider recommendations in the Monitoring Group's reports and recommend ways to improve implementation and compliance;

5. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
